Usage: find_global [-help] [<pattern> | -non_default ] [[-tcl ] | [[-name ] [-value ] [-type ] [-default ] [-info ] [-range_or_enum ] [-transient ]]]

-help              # Prints out the command usage
<pattern>          # variable name or pattern, if not given all variables are
                   # returned (string, optional)
-default           # show default value of variables (bool, optional)
-info              # show description of variables (bool, optional)
-name              # show name of variables (bool, optional)
-non_default       # return the list of variables that whose values are not the
                   # same as their default values (bool, optional)
-range_or_enum     # show range or legal enum value list if they exist
                   # (bool, optional)
-tcl               # return a tcl list that has every field value of the
                   # variables (bool, optional)
-transient         # show if variable is transient (bool, optional)
-type              # show type of variables, which is one of: bool int string
                   # enum double (bool, optional)
-value             # show current value of variables (bool, optional)